race.comment: ALNAUD (1) wound up strongly last time out to miss by a nose over 2025m at Bunbury. Delivered his Maiden over the trip there prior and keeps improving. CJP should park just off the speed and he can bounce back. SALARY MAN (7) races forward and was good beaten 1L this track and trip before a plainer effort at Toodyay back in trip. This suits better and he will get every chance from an inside gate. SLUICE BOX (3) is a veteran who has had one blip in a string of decent efforts. Placed this grade at Belmont three back and went close at Kalgoorlie the latest in stronger. May have the last crack at them. ARNRAY (2) was only beaten 2.2L at Bunbury last time showing more like his best and gets the blinkers again.
